Issue 1: footer does not meet standards with a color contrast ration of 4.5:1
footer {
    color: rgb(0, 0, 0); /* Black text */
    text-align: center;
    padding: 20px 0;
}

footer a:hover {
    color: rgb(0, 0, 0, 0.818); /* Dark gray on hover - there's a syntax error here with an extra 8 */
    text-decoration: underline;
}

Issue 1 Fix: updated css  
footer {
    color: #ffffff; /* White text */
    background-color: #333333; /* Dark gray background */
    text-align: center;
    padding: 20px 0;
}

footer a, footer a:hover {
    color: #ffffff; /* Ensuring links are also white, with an underline on hover */
    text-decoration: none; /* Default state without underline */
}

footer a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline; /* Only underline on hover */
}

